</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Association of Clinical Psychologists UK (ACP-UK) is a vital organisation representing the interests of clinical psychologists across the United Kingdom. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into the professional body, advocates for the profession and ensures high standards of practice, education, and research in clinical psychology. In an era where mental health services are more critical than ever, understanding the role of ACP-UK and adhering to the recommended best practices and regulations is essential for healthcare providers. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-1d75" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical psychology plays a pivotal role in mental health care, with clinical psychologists addressing a wide range of psychological issues. According to the NHS, one in four adults in the UK will experience a mental health problem each year. The demand for qualified clinical psychologists is growing, with an estimated 20% increase in job openings over the next five years. This underscores the importance of the ACP-UK in ensuring that professionals in this field are adequately supported and regulated.


















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Clinical psychology </strong>- A branch of psychology focused on diagnosing and treating mental, emotional, and behavioural disorders.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>ACP-UK</strong> - The Association of Clinical Psychologists UK, a professional body that supports clinical psychologists through advocacy, education, and setting practice standards.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-32_ pf-text-1"><strong>Best practices </strong>- Established methods and procedures that are accepted as superior to others because they produce results that are superior to those achieved by other means.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-36_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of ACP-UK
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Advocacy and representation</strong> - The ACP-UK plays a crucial role in advocating for the needs and interests of clinical psychologists. It engages with policymakers, healthcare providers, and other stakeholders to ensure that the voice of clinical psychologists is heard in developing mental health policies and services.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Professional Development</strong> - Continuing professional development (CPD) is essential for clinical psychologists to stay updated with the latest research, techniques, and regulations. The ACP-UK offers a variety of CPD opportunities, including workshops, seminars, and conferences, ensuring that its members are at the forefront of the field.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-43_ pf-text-1"><strong>Setting standards</strong> - The ACP-UK is instrumental in setting and maintaining high standards for clinical psychology. This includes developing guidelines and protocols that align with the latest evidence-based practices and ethical standards.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementation of legislation and regulations
