</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Integrating evidence-based practices</strong> - ACP-UK emphasises the importance of integrating evidence-based practices into clinical work. This means that clinical psychologists should use interventions and therapies that have been scientifically tested and proven effective.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Ethical practice</strong> - Maintaining high ethical standards is paramount in clinical psychology. ACP-UK provides comprehensive guidelines on ethical practice, ensuring that psychologists maintain their clients' confidentiality, autonomy, and welfare.




